<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-4460] QuorumPeer overrides Thread.getId with different semantics</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-4460</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In OpenJDK, Project Loom has significantly re-implemented java.lang.Thread. One part of this is using some of the bits in the thread identifier for non-exposed purposes. Sadly, Thread::getId is not final and it&apos;s possible that sub-classes of Thread have overridden getId to have different semantics. The JDK can defend against this but there may be 3rd party libraries that make use of Thread::getId. A corpus search of Maven central found only one class:&#160;org.apache.zookeeper.server.quorum.QuorumPeer. Does this project know why getId has been overridden to return something that is not the thread identifier?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
